Sorry about the second delayed turn in a row. I think I'm going to limit you to 3 actions per post for the next few turns, to make things easier on me.
In the Treasure Chest vote, two people voted; one voted a 1 and the other voted a 10. This comes out to an average of 5.5, which is above the requirement needed to pass a vote. (>=5)
The chest will have the following categories of items in it: Scrolls, Potions, Mob Loot, Candies, Stickers, Upgrades, Experience / Bottles o' Enchanting, Money, Plot-related Items.
Scrolls, Potions, Candies, Stickers, Upgrades, and Money should be self-explainatory.
"Mob Loot" refers to items that can be dropped by mobs, such as Eggs, Wool, Leather, or Gunpowder.
"Experience / Bottles o' Enchanting" refers to Misc EXP, skill experience, and Bottles o' Enchanting.
"Plot-related Items" refers to items that will be useful in the plot. These might not make sense right now.
This turn, the items added were mostly just consequences of things from earlier; the Prize is a result of wanting to make a unique prize for saying "smurf," for instance.
There's also the Gemmo, which requires a bit of backstory to explain. Basically, it's based off of the not-really-premium currency in the same game that inspired the Golden Food mechanic.
The Smeckledorf Smurf Hat, and the Smeckledorf Smurf, are from Theta claiming that entities called "smeckledorf smurfs" exist. It's too bad that the "make an item exist" quest expired earlier.
Then there are 10 new Stickers. What, did you not expect me to add to previous features, or something?
This also results in a new Sticker Pack, plus a third Sticker Pack capable of giving any Sticker ever.
Finally, there's the Depleted Electrum Nugget and its associated Bar. You can make tools out of these.
As for plot items, first we have what is [i]probably[/i] a thousand-degree knife (why else would it glow like that?); followed by two effects from FS1. You can't obtain these effects, so stop trying.